Associated phenotype: Recurrent Arthritis A 46 years old Turkish female who has been suffering from adult onset Still’s disease since the age of 39 was in remission with methyl prednisolone and Methotrexate treatment for 5 years. At age 39, she had experienced severe hemophagocytic syndrome at the first onset of her symptoms and she was treated with high dose steroid regimen for a couple of weeks until remission of hemophagocytic syndrome. Then methotrexate was added to her regimen and her steroid dose has been tapered gradually. She has recently been on methyl prednisolone (8 mg/day) and Methotrexate (10 mg/week). She recently is admitted to the hospital with urticarial lesions lasting for 2 months, without fever and arthralgias. Her CRP and ESR levels are slightly elevated and her ferritin level is normal. After rising of methyl prednisolon, her urticarial lesions faded away and her CRP and ESR are normalized.

Associated phenotype: TRAPS A 18 year old Turkish male patient suffering from periodic fever beginning at the age of 2. Duration of the fever has been 3-10days, which repeated in every 2-3 months. He has aphthous stomatitis during most attacks lasting 1 or 2 weeks. Cervical lymphadenopathy accompanied to some attacks. At age of 17, he experienced monoarthritis on the left hand, third PIP which lasted 1 week. He had also myalgia during febrile attacks. Colchicine was started at the age of 13, according to the result of heterozygous E148Q MEFV mutation. He did not have any other exon 2 and exon 10 mutations which were searched by sequencing.His attacks did not respond colchicine prophylaxis. During attacks, his CRP and SAA levels were elevated(e.g; CRP:20-99 mg/dl, SAA:146-980 mg/l).He responded fairly to nonsteroidal antiinflammatory drugs.
References: Erken E  Dinkçi S  Yildirim M  Eroglu A   Personal communication

Comment: A 61 year old Turkish female. She has had rare polyarticular arthritic attacks since age 12.  She has been experiencing attacks of fever, periorbital edema and maculopapular skin rashes on her face,neck and arms lasting more than 2 weeks, since age of 53. Some of her attacks accompany with polarticular arthritis. Her attacks partially responded to methyl prednisolone treatment.She has been diagnosed as Primary Sjögren's Syndrome as well, since age of 57, which was proven by minor lacrimal gland biopsy.
